**Background/Summary:**

Our app is a big boy app now and it is kinda complicated. This issue will be to consolidate some of the permission logic so that it is more verbose and intuitive. (Right now we have functions to check permissions all over the app in different places)

**Details:**

Build a function to check if the user has access to a permission

```
const initializePermission = (user: SessionUser) => (permission) => {
  const userPackages = user.packages;

  switch(permission){
    case 'APPLICATION_TABLE':
      return userPackages.length;

    case 'TALENT_NETWORK_TABLE':
      return userPackages.length && !userPackges.includes('NO_PACKAGE');

    case 'PURCHASE_CREDITS':
      return userPackages.includes('PREMIUM') || userPackages.includes('STANDARD');

    case 'EMPLOYER_CONTENT':
      return userPackages.includes('PREMIUM') || userPackages.includes('STANDARD');

    case 'SHOW_ENTREPRENEUR_CARD':
      return !userPackages.includes('PREMIUM') && !userPackages.includes('STANDARD');

    default:
      throw new Error(`${permission} is not a valid permission type, check spelling`);
  }
}
```

